{"article_id":"j6zzXXibaYC9qKjc","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The U.S. Supreme Court heard arguments Tuesday in a long-awaited set of cases","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"testing whether the federal law","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"that bars sex discrimination in employment","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"applies to LGBTQ employees .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"Specifically , the question is whether employers are free to fire employees","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"because they are gay or transgender .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"Justice Neil Gorsuch said","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"the text of Title VII of the 1964 Civil Rights Act ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"which bars discrimination","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"`` because of sex , '' or `` on the basis of sex , ''","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"appears to favor the plaintiffs in the case ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"but he wondered","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"whether the court should also consider `` the massive social upheaval ''","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"that could follow a ruling in favor of LGBTQ workers .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"The court 's conservative justices ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"who are in a majority ,","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"appeared somewhat skeptical of the arguments of the lawyers for the LGBTQ workers .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"Justice Samuel Alito , another of the court 's conservatives , said","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"if the court decided to update the statute ,","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"it might as well `` just be a legislature . ''","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"Justice Elena Kagan , one of the court 's liberal justices , said , however ,","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"that employers can not treat a man","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"who loves other men","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"differently than a woman","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"who loves men .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"At the front of these cases is Gerald Bostock ,","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"who , for 10 years , was the child-welfare coordinator for Clayton County , Ga.","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"His primary responsibility was a program","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"that provides advocates in court for abused and neglected children .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"`` It was the job","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"I loved ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"and my employer loved me doing the job , ''","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"says Bostock ,","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"noting","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"that under his leadership , the child advocates program `` reached the benchmark","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"of serving 100 % of the children in foster care , '' an `` unheard of milestone '' for any such program in the greater metro Atlanta region .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"But in 2013 , Bostock joined a gay recreational softball league .","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"And `` from that point on , my life changed , ``","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"he says .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"`` Within months , I was fired","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"for being gay .","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"I lost my livelihood .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"I lost my medical insurance","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"and at the time I was fighting prostate cancer .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"It was devastating . '' `` In truth ... even I do not fully understand it myself ''","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"Also front and center on Tuesday was Aimee Stephens .","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"She worked for the Harris Funeral Home in Livonia , Mich. , as a funeral director for six years ,","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"presenting as a man .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"But by 2012 , at age 51 , she was in despair over her gender identity","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"and contemplating suicide .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"`` I stood in the backyard for an hour with a gun to my chest ,","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"but I could n't do it , ''","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"she says .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"Stephens decided","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"she would come out at work as a transgender woman .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"For eight months , she worked on a letter to her boss and co-workers","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"telling them of her gender identity .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"`` I have realized","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"that some of you may have trouble understanding this , ''","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"she wrote ,","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"adding ,","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"`` In truth , I have had to live with it every day of my life ,","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"and even I do not fully understand it myself . ''","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"Two weeks after giving the letter to her boss ,","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"Stephens was fired .","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"Stephens and Bostock both took their former employers to court ,","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"charging","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"that their dismissals were based on sex","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"and thus violated Title VII of the 1964 Civil Rights Act .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"The owner of Harris Funeral Homes , Tom Rost , explained in a videotaped interview with his lawyers","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"that he was concerned about how the families of the deceased would react to Stephens","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"who was , in Rost 's words , `` the face of the Harris Funeral Home . ''","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"Neither Clayton County officials nor their lawyers would comment about Bostock 's firing .","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"But in their briefs , the lawyers in both cases argue","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"that Title VII of the 1964 Civil Rights Act does not apply to sexual orientation or gender status at all .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"`` Everyone understood in 1964","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"[ when the Civil Rights Act passed ]","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"that sex meant biological sex , ''","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"says John Bursch","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"who argued on behalf of Harris Funeral Homes in the Supreme Court .","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"That means that neither women nor men can be treated unequally in the work-place ,","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"he says ,","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"but that `` just does not translate into other categories '' such as sexual orientation or gender identity .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"Supporting that argument","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"are 15 states ,","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"including Texas , and its solicitor general , Kyle Hawkins .","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"The `` common-sense '' argument ,","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"he asserts ,","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"is that `` sex is not the same as sexual orientation and not the same as gender identity . ''","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"But lawyers","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"representing the fired workers","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"counter","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"that the Supreme Court over the last half-century has interpreted the law far more broadly than that .","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"They note","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"that the justices have applied the anti-discrimination statute to a variety of situations","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"that Congress was n't thinking about in 1964 .","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"For example , `` in 1964 you would n't find a single dictionary","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"that defined the term 'sexual harassment '","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"and yet the Supreme Court has held","depth":14},{"id":99,"text":"that Title VII","depth":16},{"id":100,"text":"[ of the 1964 Civil Rights Act ]","depth":16},{"id":101,"text":"prohibits sexual harassment of women '' and `` also sexual harassment of men , ''","depth":15},{"id":102,"text":"observes Stanford Law Professor Pamela Karlan .","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"The NPR Politics Podcast","depth":4},{"id":104,"text":"Abortion , Guns And LGBTQ Rights On The Docket For Supreme Court 's New Term","depth":4},{"id":105,"text":"Abortion , Guns And LGBTQ Rights On The Docket For Supreme Court 's New Term Listen · 14:48","depth":4},{"id":106,"text":"14:48","depth":4},{"id":107,"text":"Indeed , more than two decades ago , the Supreme Court ruled","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"that even same-sex sexual harassment was illegal under the statute .","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"Writing for a unanimous court ,","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"conservative Justice Antonin Scalia , said","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"while same-sex sexual harassment was `` not the principal evil","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"Congress was concerned with '' in 1964 ,","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"`` statutory provisions often go beyond the principal evil","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"to cover reasonably comparable evils . ''","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"And ,","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"`` it is ultimately the provisions of our laws , rather than the principal concerns of our legislators","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"by which we are governed . ''","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"Stanford 's Karlan ,","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"who argued for Bostock on Tuesday ,","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"reminded the justices of the court 's very first sex discrimination case after enactment of the 1964 law :","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"Phillips v. Martin Marietta Corporation .","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"At issue was an employer 's policy","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"barring the hiring of women with young children .","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"The court ruled unanimously","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"that the policy was illegal sex discrimination .","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"Karlan argues","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"that just as women with children are a subset of women","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"covered by the anti-discrimination law ,","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"so too are gay , lesbian and bisexual employees .","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"`` If it 's sex discrimination to say ,","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"'You ca n't work for us","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"if you are a woman","depth":15},{"id":135,"text":"and you have children at home ,","depth":15},{"id":136,"text":"it 's also sex discrimination to say","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"you ca n't work for us","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"because you 're a woman","depth":15},{"id":139,"text":"and you have a wife at home , ' ``","depth":15},{"id":140,"text":"says Karlan .","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"Similarly ,","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"she maintains ,","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"`` If you would n't fire a man","depth":14},{"id":144,"text":"for marrying a woman ,","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"but you would fire a woman","depth":14},{"id":146,"text":"for marrying a woman ,","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"you 've discriminated against the woman","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"who works for you . ''","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"The argument for transgender employees may be more politically difficult to sell .","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"But it is arguably more stark .","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"It goes like this :","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"If an employer hires a man","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"and later fires the employee","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"when the employee shows up as a woman ,","depth":13},{"id":155,"text":"how is that not discrimination","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"based on sex ?","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"Lawyer Bursch will tell the justices","depth":7},{"id":158,"text":"that sexual orientation and gender status simply do not fit under the 1964 anti-discrimination formula .","depth":7},{"id":159,"text":"He warns","depth":8},{"id":160,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":161,"text":"if the court were to rule against the employers in these cases ,","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"it would have ramifications beyond employment .","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"`` If we redefine the meaning of sex in federal law , ''","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"he predicts ,","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"it would allow `` biological men to identify as women","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"and take women 's places on sports teams . ''","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"Bursch argues","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"that has already happened in some places ,","depth":10},{"id":169,"text":"with cisgender women losing out in medals to transgender women .","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"Federal law does indeed bar sex discrimination in sports programs at schools","depth":7},{"id":171,"text":"that get federal money .","depth":7},{"id":172,"text":"And the NCAA has developed regulations","depth":8},{"id":173,"text":"for when trans student-athletes may or may not participate .","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"But","depth":9},{"id":175,"text":"as Stanford 's Karlan observes ,","depth":10},{"id":176,"text":"Title IX ,","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"best known for its impact","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"in advancing women 's sports ,","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"`` is a different statute . ''","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"And the regulations for education funding under Title IX `` are different than the rules in the workplace '' under Title VII .","depth":8},{"id":181,"text":"Lawyers for the employers respond","depth":6},{"id":182,"text":"that Congress in 1964 simply did not anticipate the questions","depth":9},{"id":183,"text":"raised in these cases","depth":9},{"id":184,"text":"about the scope of Title VII","depth":8},{"id":185,"text":"and that Congress , not the courts , should be addressing these issues .","depth":7},{"id":186,"text":"The case has drawn even more attention","depth":6},{"id":187,"text":"than anticipated ,","depth":6},{"id":188,"text":"with dozens of friend-of-the-court briefs on each side .","depth":5},{"id":189,"text":"Siding with the employers are business groups","depth":7},{"id":190,"text":"that , for the most part , have some religious affiliation .","depth":7},{"id":191,"text":"But weighing in on the other side , in favor of protection for gay and trans employees ,","depth":7},{"id":192,"text":"are 206 major corporations","depth":8},{"id":193,"text":"that employ over 7 million workers .","depth":8},{"id":194,"text":"The Trump administration ,","depth":7},{"id":195,"text":"reversing the position of the Obama administration ,","depth":7},{"id":196,"text":"will argue in the Supreme Court against the LGBTQ employees .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":393,"left":299,"right":392,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":299,"left":221,"right":298,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":221,"left":202,"right":220,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":200,"right":201,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":0,"right":199,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":198,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":198,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":201,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":220,"left":209,"right":219,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":209,"left":206,"right":208,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":206,"left":6,"right":205,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":205,"left":204,"right":10,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":204,"left":7,"right":203,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":203,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":208,"left":11,"right":207,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":207,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":219,"left":214,"right":218,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":214,"left":211,"right":213,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":211,"left":210,"right":16,"relation":